[2] Viet Nam
Date: Tue, 20 Jul 2004 20:30:16 +0900 (JST)
From: ProMED <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhuanet 20 Jul 2004 [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2004-07/20/content_1618658.htm>
<http://www.chinaview.cn 2004-07-20 16:15:45>

Dengue fever kills more people in Viet Nam
--------------------------------------
As of 19 Jul 2004, dengue fever has claimed 50 lives in Viet Nam, a
year-on-year increase of nearly 100 percent. The disease has affected a
total of 31 700 people in the period, doubling the figure in the same
period of 2003, according to local newspaper Youth, on Tuesday.
Most of the dengue fever sufferers and deaths are from the country's
southern region, whose weather is most favorable for the development of
mosquitoes that are the main transmitter.
To deal with the situation, the Ministry of Health has just launched an
urgent program on dengue fever prevention nationwide, called for local
health agencies to promote information campaigns among residents, and
supplied localities with more mosquito-killing chemicals, medicines and
equipment.
Vietnam reported 35 073 cases of dengue fever infections, including 58
fatalities last year [2003], up 48 percent and 45 percent against the
previous year [2002], respectively.
