[4] Singapore
Date: Sun, 18 Jul 2004 21:50:55 -0300
From: ProMED <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The New Paper, Singapore 17 Jul 2004 [edited]
<http://newpaper.asia1.com.sg/top/story/0,4136,68009-1090079940,00.html?>

The number of dengue cases so far in 2004 is 2550, slightly lower than the
2780 cases reported for the same period in 2003, but still considered high.
NEA is continuing with surveillance and control in the area and working to
alert the residents about dengue through flyers and banners. Education
efforts are also underway on how to prevent mosquito breeding.
[Byline: Teh Jen Lee <jenlee@sph.com.sg>]
